  "hn_post": "mylib 1.4.0 is out. Two changes worth flagging for anyone using it in production.\n\nStreaming: every API call now accepts stream=True. On long generations we measured time-to-first-token dropping by roughly 60%. If you're rendering tokens progressively in a UI, that's the bigger of the two changes.\n\nToken budgets: max_tokens is configurable per-request or in the global config. The motivating case was batch jobs — a misbehaving prompt or a loop bug in caller code could previously rack up real spend before anyone noticed. Now it just stops at the cap.\n\nOne breaking change: client.complete() is removed. It's been deprecated since 1.2 with a warning, but the code is gone in 1.4. Replacement is client.messages.create() with the same arguments.\n\npip install mylib==1.4.0\nhttps://github.com/acme/mylib/releases/tag/v1.4.0",
